      <h2 class="c-title u-vertical-space">Nara Park</h2>
      <!-- /c-title -->


      <div class="s-entry-content u-vertical-space">
        <p><strong>(Travel Time: 30 minutes)</strong></p>
        <p>Just a short distance outside of Osaka on the picturesque Kintetsu Railway Express Line is a little slice of heaven in the form of Nara Park and its thousand-plus wild deer. Calm and friendly all year round thanks to long-term exposure to tourists, these beautiful and gentle creatures will double their affection if you’ve picked up some senbei (deer food) from any one of the many vendors scattered around the park (a few deer have even learned to bow in exchange for snacks).</p>
      </div>
      <!-- /s-entry-content -->


      <div class="u-vertical-space">
        <img src="{{ cdn }}images/nara-koen-park.jpg" alt="">
      </div>
      <!-- /u-vertical-space -->


      <div class="c-content-block c-content-block--narrow c-content-block--white u-vertical-space">

        <h3 class="c-title c-content-block__title u-vertical-space u-vertical-space--small">Also Nearby</h3>
        <!-- /c-title -->


        <div class="s-entry-content u-vertical-space u-vertical-space--small">
          <p><strong>Todaiji Temple​:</strong> home to the country’s largest Buddha statue.</p>
          <p><strong>Kagusa Taisha Shrine​:</strong> Nara’s most beloved Shinto shrine; famed for its hundreds of bronze lanterns.</p>
        </div>
